mcmT1E1CsuCfgTable.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTable
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The T1/E1 CSU Configuration table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgEntry.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgEntry
mcmT1E1CsuCfgEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the T1/E1 CSU Configuration \ table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgifIndex.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgifIndex
mcmT1E1CsuCfgifIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The T1E1 Csu Cfg interface index \ value of the specifc entry.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineType.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineType
mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineType.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object determines \ whether the line is a T1 CSU or E1 CSU.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineSpeed.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineSpeed
mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineSpeed.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1/E1 CSU \ total configured DS0 line speed.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineBuildOut.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineBuildOut
mcmT1E1CsuCfgLineBuildOut.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1/E1 CSU \ line build out. For a T1 CSU, the default value \ is neg-7pt5-db (6). For an E1 CSU, the default \ value is either ohm-75-normal (9) (an E1 CSU interface \ with 2 BNC connectors) or ohm-120-normal (10) \ (an E1 CSU interface with an RJ48 connector). \ Note that the ranges of enumeration values 1-8 and \ 9-15 apply uniquely to T1 and E1 interfaces; respectively.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxIdleCode.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxIdleCode
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxIdleCode.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1/E1 CSU \ transmit idle code. For a T1 CSU, the default value is \ hex 0x7F. For an E1 CSU, the default value is hex 0x55.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxClkSource.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxClkSource
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxClkSource.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1/E1 CSU \ line clocking source.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgDS0BasicRate.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgDS0BasicRate
mcmT1E1CsuCfgDS0BasicRate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1/E1 CSU \ line speed to be a multiple of the specified \ basic rate. E.g., Line Speed 256K = 4 x 64K.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgLocalLoopback.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgLocalLoopback
mcmT1E1CsuCfgLocalLoopback.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1/E1 CSU \ local loopback.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgRemoteLoopback.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgRemoteLoopback
mcmT1E1CsuCfgRemoteLoopback.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1/E1 CSU \ remote loopback.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgFramerLoopback.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgFramerLoopback
mcmT1E1CsuCfgFramerLoopback.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1/E1 CSU \ framer loopback.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTrapEnable.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTrapEnable
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTrapEnable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects whether the T1/E1 \ CSU traps should be generated for this interface.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgFrameFmt.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgFrameFmt
mcmT1E1CsuCfgFrameFmt.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1 CSU \ frame format. \ Note that for an E1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRx0CodeSuppress.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRx0CodeSuppress
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRx0CodeSuppress.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects zero \ code suppression for a T1 CSU interface. \ Note that for an E1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxB7ZeroSuppress.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxB7ZeroSuppress
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxB7ZeroSuppress.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects bit 7 zero\ suppression for a T1 CSU interface. Selects stuffing \ bit 7 to 1 if 8 consecutive zeros occurred. \ Note that for an E1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = b7zsDisable (1): no stuffing occurred. \ b7zsEnable (2): bit 7 forced to a one in \ channels with all zeros.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgPayloadLoopback.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgPayloadLoopback
mcmT1E1CsuCfgPayloadLoopback.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1 CSU \ payload loopback. \ Note that for an E1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTransmitLoopUp.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTransmitLoopUp
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTransmitLoopUp.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1 CSU \ transmit loop up. \ Note that for an E1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTransmitLoopDown.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTransmitLoopDown
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTransmitLoopDown.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the T1 CSU \ transmit loop down. \ Note that for an E1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxHDB3.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxHDB3
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxHDB3.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the E1 CSU HDB3. \ Note that for a T1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxCRC4.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxCRC4
mcmT1E1CsuCfgTxRxCRC4.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the E1 CSU CRC4. \ Note that for a T1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCfgDS0Connection.name: mcmT1E1CsuCfgDS0Connection
mcmT1E1CsuCfgDS0Connection.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the DS0 \ channels for the T1/E1 CSU line connection. \ Valid characters are decimal digits, comma \ (','), and hyphen ('-').; HELP = Comma (',') is used as a delimiter between \ individual channel selections. \ e.g., 13,16 means DS0 channels 13 and 16. \ Hyphen ('-') is used only in Set operations \ to indicate a range of DS0 channels. \ e.g., 2,5-8 means DS0 channels 2,5,6,7, and 8.; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgTable.name: mcmCsuCfgTable
mcmCsuCfgTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The 56K CSU Configuration table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_CFG, VPN_CFG;

mcmCsuCfgEntry.name: mcmCsuCfgEntry
mcmCsuCfgEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the 56K CSU Configuration \ table.); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgifIndex.name: mcmCsuCfgifIndex
mcmCsuCfgifIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The 56k Csu Cfg interface index \ value of the specifc entry.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgOperatingMode.name: mcmCsuCfgOperatingMode
mcmCsuCfgOperatingMode.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the 56K CSU \ operating mode.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgClockingSource.name: mcmCsuCfgClockingSource
mcmCsuCfgClockingSource.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object selects the 56K CSU \ clocking source.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgTxOutOfFrame.name: mcmCsuCfgTxOutOfFrame
mcmCsuCfgTxOutOfFrame.description: NAME = ; DESC = This object selects transmission of the 56K CSU \ Out Of Frame sequence for DDS-PRI mode, or \ transmission of Multiplexer Out Of Sync \ sequence for DDS-SC mode.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgTxOutOfService.name: mcmCsuCfgTxOutOfService
mcmCsuCfgTxOutOfService.description: NAME = ; DESC = This object selects transmission of the 56K CSU \ Out Of Service sequence for DDS-PRI mode, or \ transmission of Abnormal Station Code \ sequence for DDS-SC mode.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgTxControlModeIdle.name: mcmCsuCfgTxControlModeIdle
mcmCsuCfgTxControlModeIdle.description: NAME = ; DESC = This object selects transmission of the 56K CSU \ Control Mode Idle sequence.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgZeroSuppressDisable.name: mcmCsuCfgZeroSuppressDisable
mcmCsuCfgZeroSuppressDisable.description: NAME = ; DESC = This object selects the 56K CSU disable \ transmit Zero Suppression for DDS-PRI mode, \ or transmission of all zeros for DDS-SC mode.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgTxIdle.name: mcmCsuCfgTxIdle
mcmCsuCfgTxIdle.description: NAME = ; DESC = This object selects transmission of the 56K CSU \ All Marks (or 1s) of the Data Mode Idle sequence \ for all the modes.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgCSULoopback.name: mcmCsuCfgCSULoopback
mcmCsuCfgCSULoopback.description: NAME = ; DESC = This object selects the 56K CSU to force the CSU \ to be in a loopback mode.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgFilterForceEnable.name: mcmCsuCfgFilterForceEnable
mcmCsuCfgFilterForceEnable.description: NAME = ; DESC = This object selects the 56K CSU to have \ filter forcing enabled or not.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuCfgFilterForcingCntl.name: mcmCsuCfgFilterForcingCntl
mcmCsuCfgFilterForcingCntl.description: NAME = ; DESC = This object selects the 56K CSU filter \ gain if filter force is enabled.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CsuCntlRegStatusTable.name: mcmT1E1CsuCntlRegStatusTable
mcmT1E1CsuCntlRegStatusTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The T1/E1 CSU Control Register Status \ table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_DISP, VPN_DISP;

mcmT1E1CsuCntlRegStatusEntry.name: mcmT1E1CsuCntlRegStatusEntry
mcmT1E1CsuCntlRegStatusEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the T1/E1 CSU Control Register \ Status table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusifIndex.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusifIndex
mcmT1E1CSUStatusifIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The T1E1 CSU Status interface index \ value of the specifc entry.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg1.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg1
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg1.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates RCR1, the \ value of Receive Control Register 1 for a T1/E1 \ CSU line type.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg2.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg2
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg2.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates RCR2, the \ value of Receive Control Register 2 for a T1/E1 \ CSU line type.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg3.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg3
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg3.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates TCR1, the \ value of Transmit Control Register 1 for a T1/E1 \ CSU line type.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg4.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg4
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg4.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates TCR2, the \ value of Transmit Control Register 2 for a T1/E1 \ CSU line type.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg5.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg5
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg5.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates CCR1, the \ value of Common Control Register 1 for a T1/E1 \ CSU line type.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg6.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg6
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg6.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates CCR2, the \ value of Common Control Register 2 for a T1/E1 \ CSU line type.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg7.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg7
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg7.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates CCR3, the \ value of Common Control Register 3 for a T1/E1 \ CSU line type.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg8.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg8
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg8.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates LICR, the value of \ the Line Interface Control Register for a T1 CSU line type.\ The value of this object indicates CCR4, the value of \ Common Control Register 4 for an E1 line type.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg9.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg9
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg9.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates CCR5, the \ value of Common Control Register 5 for an E1 CSU \ line type. \ Note that for a T1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg10.name: mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg10
mcmT1E1CSUStatusCntlReg10.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates LICR, the \ value of the Line Interface Control Register for \ an E1 CSU line type. \ Note that for a T1 CSU interface, this object is not used.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES =;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusTable.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusTable
mcmT1CsuGenStatusTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The T1 CSU General Status and \ Statistics table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_DISP, VPN_DISP;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusEntry.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusEntry
mcmT1CsuGenStatusEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the T1 CSU General \ Status and Statistics table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusifIndex.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusifIndex
mcmT1CsuGenStatusifIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The T1 CSU General Status interface \ index value of the specifc entry.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusLineStatus.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusLineStatus
mcmT1CsuGenStatusLineStatus.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ T1 CSU line status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRedAlarm.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRedAlarm
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRedAlarm.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ T1 CSU red alarm status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusYellowAlarm.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusYellowAlarm
mcmT1CsuGenStatusYellowAlarm.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ T1 CSU yellow alarm status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusBlueAlarm.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusBlueAlarm
mcmT1CsuGenStatusBlueAlarm.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ T1 CSU blue alarm status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLevel.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLevel
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLevel.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU line receive level status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrFull.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrFull
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrFull.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU receive elastic store full status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrEmpty.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrEmpty
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrEmpty.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU receive elastic store empty status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxPlsDensViolate.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxPlsDensViolate
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxPlsDensViolate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU receive pulse density violation status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusTxPlsDensViolate.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusTxPlsDensViolate
mcmT1CsuGenStatusTxPlsDensViolate.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU transmit pulse density violation status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxCarrierLoss.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxCarrierLoss
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxCarrierLoss.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU receive carrier loss status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxSyncLoss.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxSyncLoss
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxSyncLoss.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU receive loss of sync status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusLnCdViolations.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusLnCdViolations
mcmT1CsuGenStatusLnCdViolations.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the number \ of T1 CSU line code violations. \ Note that this is a 16-bit counter.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLoopUpCdDetect.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLoopUpCdDetect
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLoopUpCdDetect.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU receive loop up code status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLoopDnCdDetect.name: mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLoopDnCdDetect
mcmT1CsuGenStatusRxLoopDnCdDetect.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the T1 \ CSU receive loop down code status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusTable.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusTable
mcmE1CsuGenStatusTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The E1 CSU General Status and \ Statistics table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_DISP, VPN_DISP;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusEntry.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusEntry
mcmE1CsuGenStatusEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the E1 CSU General \ Status and Statistics table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusifIndex.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusifIndex
mcmE1CsuGenStatusifIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The E1 CSU General Status interface \ index value of the specifc entry.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusLineStatus.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusLineStatus
mcmE1CsuGenStatusLineStatus.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ E1 CSU line status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusRedAlarm.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusRedAlarm
mcmE1CsuGenStatusRedAlarm.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ E1 CSU red alarm status. It includes both \ receive carrier loss and receive loss of sync.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusRemoteAlarm.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusRemoteAlarm
mcmE1CsuGenStatusRemoteAlarm.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ E1 CSU remote alarm status. It includes both \ receive remote alarm and receive distant MF \ alarm.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusAISAlarm.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusAISAlarm
mcmE1CsuGenStatusAISAlarm.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ E1 CSU AIS Alarm status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxCarrierLoss.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxCarrierLoss
mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxCarrierLoss.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the \ E1 CSU receive carrier loss status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxSyncLoss.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxSyncLoss
mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxSyncLoss.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the E1 \ CSU receive loss of sync status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusTxElasStrFull.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusTxElasStrFull
mcmE1CsuGenStatusTxElasStrFull.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the E1 \ CSU transmit elastic store full status. This \ indicates that the E1 CSU transmit side \ elastic store buffer fills and a frame is deleted.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusTxElasStrEmpty.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusTxElasStrEmpty
mcmE1CsuGenStatusTxElasStrEmpty.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the E1 \ CSU transmit elastic store empty status. This \ indicates that the E1 CSU transmit side elastic \ store buffer empties and a frame is repeated.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrFull.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrFull
mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrFull.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the E1 \ CSU receive elastic store full status. This \ indicates that the E1 CSU receive side elastic \ store buffer fills and a frame is deleted.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrEmpty.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrEmpty
mcmE1CsuGenStatusRxElasStrEmpty.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the E1 \ CSU receive elastic store empty status. This \ indicates that the E1 CSU receive side elastic \ store buffer empties and a frame is repeated.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusBpvOrLnCdViolations.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusBpvOrLnCdViolations
mcmE1CsuGenStatusBpvOrLnCdViolations.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the number \ of E1 CSU line code violations. \ Bipolar violation counts if HDB3 disabled, code \ violation counts if HDB3 enabled. \ Note that this is a 16-bit counter.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusFASErrors.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusFASErrors
mcmE1CsuGenStatusFASErrors.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the number \ of E1 CSU FAS error counts. FAS error counts \ record word errors in the frame alignment \ signal in timeslot 0. \ Note that this is a 12-bit counter.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmE1CsuGenStatusCRC4Errors.name: mcmE1CsuGenStatusCRC4Errors
mcmE1CsuGenStatusCRC4Errors.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the number \ of E1 CSU CRC4 error counts. This object \ is only applicable when CRC4 is enabled. \ Note that this is a 10-bit counter.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusTable.name: mcmCsuStatusTable
mcmCsuStatusTable.description: NAME = ; DESC = The 56K CSU Status and Statistics table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = NET_DISP, VPN_DISP;

mcmCsuStatusEntry.name: mcmCsuStatusEntry
mcmCsuStatusEntry.description: NAME = ; DESC = An entry in the 56K CSU Status \ and Statistics table.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusifIndex.name: mcmCsuStatusifIndex
mcmCsuStatusifIndex.description: NAME = ; DESC = The 56k CSU Status interface index \ value of the specifc entry.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusLineStatus.name: mcmCsuStatusLineStatus
mcmCsuStatusLineStatus.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the 56K \ CSU line status.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusRxLossOfSignal.name: mcmCsuStatusRxLossOfSignal
mcmCsuStatusRxLossOfSignal.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates if the 56K \ CSU receiver has lost signal.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusFAWSync.name: mcmCsuStatusFAWSync
mcmCsuStatusFAWSync.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the 56K \ CSU DDS FAW Sync in DDS-SC or CC-64K.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusLoopPresent.name: mcmCsuStatusLoopPresent
mcmCsuStatusLoopPresent.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates if the 56K \ CSU loop is currently present.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusInsertLossLineLength.name: mcmCsuStatusInsertLossLineLength
mcmCsuStatusInsertLossLineLength.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the 56K \ CSU receiver Insertion loss (iL) in db, and \ Line Length (LL) in kilometers.; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusRxSignalMag.name: mcmCsuStatusRxSignalMag
mcmCsuStatusRxSignalMag.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates the 56K \ CSU receive signal magnitude expressed as \ the 'receiver slicer level'. This value \ is used in conjunction with the db Insertion \ Loss ('iL' from InsertLossLineLength object) \ to compute the signal magnitude as follows: \ Nyquist frequency loop attn (in db) = \ [(iL)**2 + 20log10(51/RxSignalMag)].; HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmCsuStatusInvalidBPVcounts.name: mcmCsuStatusInvalidBPVcounts

mcmT1CsuRedAlarmSet.name: mcmT1CsuRedAlarmSet
mcmT1CsuRedAlarmSet.description: NAME = ; DESC = When a downstream node detects a loss of \ synchronization in its receive pair of a \ T1 line, it is in red alarm condition. \ Severity Level: CRITICAL.; HELP = ;

mcmT1CsuRedAlarmClear.name: mcmT1CsuRedAlarmClear
mcmT1CsuRedAlarmClear.description: NAME = ; DESC = When a downstream node is back in \ synchronization with its receive pair \ of a T1 line. This trap clears the node \ that has the Red Alarm condition. \ Severity Level : INFORMATIVE.; HELP = ;

mcmT1CsuYellowAlarmSet.name: mcmT1CsuYellowAlarmSet
mcmT1CsuYellowAlarmSet.description: NAME = ; DESC = When a downstream node detects a loss of \ synchronization in its receive pair of a \ T1 line, it is in red alarm condition. \ In turn, it transmits a yellow alarm \ signal upstream to the previous node. \ Severity Level: MAJOR.; HELP = ;

mcmT1CsuYellowAlarmClear.name: mcmT1CsuYellowAlarmClear
mcmT1CsuYellowAlarmClear.description: NAME = ; DESC = When a downstream node detects a loss of \ synchronization in its receive pair of a \ T1 line, it is in red alarm condition. \ In turn, it transmits a yellow alarm \ signal upstream to the previous node. \ This trap clears the node that has the \ Yellow Alarm condition.; Severity Level: INFORMATIVE.; HELP = ;

mcmT1CsuBlueAlarmSet.name: mcmT1CsuBlueAlarmSet
mcmT1CsuBlueAlarmSet.description: NAME = ; DESC = When a downstream node detects a loss of \ synchronization in its receive pair of a \ T1 line, it is in red alarm condition. \ In turn, it transmits a yellow alarm \ signal upstream to the previous node \ and a blue alarm signal downstream to \ the next node.\ Severity Level: MINOR.; HELP = ;

mcmT1CsuBlueAlarmClear.name: mcmT1CsuBlueAlarmClear
mcmT1CsuBlueAlarmClear.description: NAME = ; DESC = When a downstream node detects a loss of \ synchronization in its receive pair of a \ T1 line, it is in red alarm condition. \ In turn, it transmits a yellow alarm \ signal upstream to the previous node \ and a blue alarm signal downstream to \ the next node. This trap clears the \ node that has the Blue Alarm condition. \ Severity Level: INFORMATIVE.; HELP = ;

mcmE1CsuRedAlarmSet.name: mcmE1CsuRedAlarmSet
mcmE1CsuRedAlarmSet.description: NAME = ; DESC = This trap is generated upon the occurrence \ of an E1 CSU Red Alarm. A red alarm indicates that \ an out-of-frame condition existed for the last 100 \ milliseconds or longer. \ Severity Level: CRITICAL.; HELP = ;

mcmE1CsuRedAlarmClear.name: mcmE1CsuRedAlarmClear
mcmE1CsuRedAlarmClear.description: NAME = ; DESC = This trap is generated upon the clearance \ of an E1 CSU Red Alarm. A red alarm is cleared \ when the out-of-frame condition has been absent \ for 100 milliseconds. \ Severity Level : INFORMATIVE.; HELP = ;

mcmE1CsuRemoteAlarmSet.name: mcmE1CsuRemoteAlarmSet
mcmE1CsuRemoteAlarmSet.description: NAME = ; DESC = This trap is generated upon the occurrence \ of an E1 CSU Remote Alarm. \ Severity Level: MAJOR.; HELP = ;

mcmE1CsuRemoteAlarmClear.name: mcmE1CsuRemoteAlarmClear
mcmE1CsuRemoteAlarmClear.description: NAME = ; DESC = This trap is generated upon the clearance \ of an E1 CSU Remote Alarm. \ Severity Level: INFORMATIVE.; HELP = ;

mcmE1CsuAISAlarmSet.name: mcmE1CsuAISAlarmSet
mcmE1CsuAISAlarmSet.description: NAME = ; DESC = This trap is generated upon the occurrence \ of an E1 CSU AIS Alarm. The AIS (alarm indication \ signal) alarm is detected as an all ones condition \ on the E1 line persisting for 100ms or longer. \ This indicates the E1 line is unavailable. \ Severity Level: MINOR.; HELP = ;

mcmE1CsuAISAlarmClear.name: mcmE1CsuAISAlarmClear
mcmE1CsuAISAlarmClear.description: NAME = ; DESC = This trap is generated upon the clearance \ of an E1 CSU AIS Alarm. \ Severity Level: INFORMATIVE.; HELP = ;
